---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Nectar Hydration — JWM" activePage="work">

  <div class="case-block">
    <div class="case-header">
      <div>
        <p class="case-eyebrow">01 — Mid-market · Subscription migration</p>
        <h1 class="case-title">Nectar <em>Hydration</em></h1>
        <p class="case-summary">A white glove migration that started as a standard pre-sales engagement and expanded into frontend development, product team coordination, and business strategy consulting — all under a six-week deadline that would normally take 90 days.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="case-meta">
        <div class="meta-item">
          <p class="meta-label">Segment</p>
          <p class="meta-value"><strong>Mid-market</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-divider"></div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <p class="meta-label">Timeline</p>
          <p class="meta-value"><strong>6 weeks</strong> (vs. 90-day standard)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-divider"></div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <p class="meta-label">My scope</p>
          <p class="meta-value">Pre-sales · Frontend dev · Biz strategy · Product coordination</p>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-divider"></div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <p class="meta-label">Status</p>
          <p class="meta-value status-live">Live &lt;3 months — metrics trending up</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="case-body">
      <nav class="case-nav">
        <span class="case-nav-item active">The brief</span>
        <span class="case-nav-item">The problems</span>
        <span class="case-nav-item">My approach</span>
        <span class="case-nav-item">Key insight</span>
        <span class="case-nav-item">Outcomes</span>
        <span class="case-nav-item">Learnings</span>
      </nav>

      <div class="case-content">

        <div class="content-section">
          <p class="content-label">The brief</p>
          <p class="prose">Nectar Hydration came to Recharge looking to migrate their subscription program from a competitor platform. Standard enough on the surface — but two things made this atypical from the start. First, the engagement was part of a new <strong>white glove VIP migration motion</strong>, meaning Recharge would take on full responsibility for the migration including frontend development — something we don't normally do on behalf of merchants. Second, they wanted to be <strong>live in six weeks</strong>. Our standard onboarding and migration timeline is 90 days.</p>
          <p class="prose">My AE set the tone early: <em>"Everything they want, we will find a solution for."</em> That framing was liberating and pressure-filled in equal measure. I was responsible for pre-sales discovery, business strategy recommendations, solutioning — and also for the <strong>Shopify Liquid frontend development</strong> needed to keep their existing PDPs intact and compatible with Recharge's selling plans.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
          <p class="content-label">The problems</p>
          <div class="problem-grid">
            <div class="problem-card">
              <p class="problem-title">Weak cancellation flow</p>
              <p class="problem-desc">Limited customization on their existing cancellation experience meant subscribers were churning without any meaningful retention intervention.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="problem-card">
              <p class="problem-title">Poor retention tooling</p>
              <p class="problem-desc">No tailored cancellation prevention offers. Both passive and active retention rates were underperforming relative to category benchmarks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="problem-card">
              <p class="problem-title">Limited brand experience</p>
              <p class="problem-desc">Needed dynamic, branded customer-facing experiences and A/B testing capability — neither of which their current platform could support.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="problem-card">
              <p class="problem-title">Analytics gaps</p>
              <p class="problem-desc">Required robust analytics with filtering by product, order cycle, and SKU segmentation. Their existing reporting was too blunt for the decisions they needed to make.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
          <p class="content-label">My approach</p>
          <div class="step-flow">
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">01</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <p class="step-title">Discovery under constraint</p>
                <p class="step-detail">Nectar's team was not forthright with information — they were often unaware of how their own business was configured day-to-day, and had limited opinions on how they should communicate with their customers. That meant I was making a lot of assumptions and validating them in real time. I treated each discovery session as a hypothesis test, not a Q&amp;A.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">02</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <p class="step-title">Frontend development — PDP migration</p>
                <p class="step-detail">Their existing product detail pages had specialized widgets that needed to remain intact and be made compatible with Recharge's selling plans. I handled the <strong>Shopify Liquid development</strong> end-to-end — building and validating the integration between their custom frontend components and Recharge's subscription architecture.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">03</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <p class="step-title">Feature strategy recommendations</p>
                <p class="step-detail">Beyond the technical migration, I advised on which Recharge features to enable for maximum lift — retention flows, cancellation prevention offers, branded customer portal configuration, and analytics instrumentation.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">04</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <p class="step-title">Product team coordination</p>
                <p class="step-detail">Moving at 2.5x the normal migration pace required tight alignment with Recharge's internal Product team. I coordinated across timelines, flagged blockers early, and kept the merchant-facing delivery on track without letting internal dependencies become the merchant's problem.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">05</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <p class="step-title">Business strategy consulting</p>
                <p class="step-detail">I identified several areas where Nectar's existing business logic was working against them — including a discounting structure that was actively discouraging higher order quantities.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
          <p class="content-label">Key insight — the discount ceiling problem</p>
          <div class="insight-block">
            <p class="insight-block__label">Business strategy finding</p>
            <p class="insight-block__text">Nectar's existing discount structure was <strong>quantity-based, capping at $76 off for 4+ products</strong>. The problem: a customer adding 7 items to their cart received the exact same discount as a customer adding 4. There was no incentive to order more — and in practice, the structure was actively signalling to customers that 4 items was the ceiling worth caring about.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="prose">I built an Excel model to map this out visually — showing the effective per-unit discount rate at each quantity tier and illustrating exactly where the structure stopped rewarding the customer. My recommendation was to <strong>shift to a per-unit discount model</strong> that preserved the discount value at lower quantities but continued to reward customers proportionally as order size increased.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote">"The discount structure was telling customers that 4 items was the right answer. We needed it to say: more is always better."</div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
          <p class="content-label">Outcomes</p>
          <p class="prose">Nectar has been live on Recharge for under three months. Early indicators are moving in the right direction across every dimension we targeted.</p>
          <div class="outcome-stats">
            <div class="stat-cell">
              <p class="stat-value">↑</p>
              <p class="stat-label">Passive retention rate</p>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-cell">
              <p class="stat-value">↑</p>
              <p class="stat-label">Active retention rate</p>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-cell">
              <p class="stat-value">↑</p>
              <p class="stat-label">Subscription conversion at checkout</p>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-cell">
              <p class="stat-value">↑</p>
              <p class="stat-label">AOV &amp; LTV</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="prose">Specific numbers are omitted out of respect for the merchant's confidentiality. The directional signal across all four metrics — within 90 days of go-live — is what matters here.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
          <p class="content-label">What I'd do differently</p>
          <div class="learnings-list">
            <div class="learning-item"><strong>Establish information-gathering protocols earlier.</strong> Working with founders and owners who aren't close to day-to-day operations requires a different discovery approach. I'd build in explicit alignment sessions upfront to document assumptions and get sign-off before building on them.</div>
            <div class="learning-item"><strong>Push harder for a communication strategy conversation.</strong> Nectar lacked a clear view of how they wanted to communicate with subscribers. That ambiguity slowed some feature decisions. In hindsight I'd have prioritized that conversation in week one, not week four.</div>
            <div class="learning-item"><strong>Document the non-standard scope explicitly.</strong> This engagement stretched well beyond a typical SE remit. Clearer upfront scoping of what was in-bounds would have helped set expectations across all parties, including internally.</div>
            <div class="learning-item"><strong>The 6-week timeline was achievable, but fragile.</strong> We hit it, but there was limited margin for error. For future VIP migrations, I'd advocate for a structured fast-track process with predefined gates rather than compressing the standard process end-to-end.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="case-footer">
    <a href={`${base}work`} class="case-footer__back">← Back to all work</a>
    <a href={`${base}work/faster-way`} class="case-footer__next">Next: FASTer Way →</a>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .case-block { padding: 5rem 3rem; position: relative; z-index: 1; }

  .case-header {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .case-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-top: 6rem;
  }
  .case-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.5vw, 3rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .case-title em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .case-summary {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 580px;
  }

  .case-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    min-width: 210px;
    margin-top: 6rem;
  }
  .meta-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }
  .meta-value { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }
  .meta-value strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }
  .meta-divider { width: 100%; height: 1px; background: var(--border); }
  .status-live { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }

  .case-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .case-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 7rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .case-nav-item {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .case-nav-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .case-nav-item.active { color: var(--accent); background: rgba(200,240,84,0.04); }

  .case-content { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3rem; }
  .content-section { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; }
  .content-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .problem-card { background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .problem-card:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .problem-title {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .problem-title::before { content: '↳'; color: var(--accent); margin-right: 0.5rem; }
  .problem-desc { font-size: 0.78rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  .step-flow { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .step-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 44px 1fr;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .step-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-item:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .step-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 1.4rem 0 1.25rem 1rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .step-content { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; }
  .step-title { font-size: 0.87rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .step-detail { font-size: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .step-detail strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  .outcome-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .stat-cell { background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; text-align: center; }
  .stat-value { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .stat-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .learnings-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .learning-item {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .learning-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .learning-item strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  .insight-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .insight-block__label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .insight-block__text { font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .insight-block__text strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  .pull-quote {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .prose { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .prose strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }
  .prose em { font-style: italic; }

  .case-footer {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 2rem 3rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .case-footer__back,
  .case-footer__next {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .case-footer__back:hover,
  .case-footer__next:hover { color: var(--accent); }
</style>